The paper proposes a deep learning framework for skill assessment in surgical training using motion kinematics data. This involves the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) to map multivariate time series data to individual skill levels. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) since the paper involves the use of CNNs. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of robot-assisted surgery, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) another likely category. The paper also involves the use of data-driven approaches, which makes cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. Finally, the paper involves the use of objective skill assessment, which makes cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) another likely category.
